      },
      "date": "2015-02-20 13:04:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIt would have been nicer to separate the minor PPC-specific fixes (looks like only (unsigned long long) casts) from the major code reorg for clang.  That makes it really hard to see what you actually changed.\n\nThat said, it doesn't break anything, and is definitely an improvement over what was there before.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9c68851eab5ec14db1fb2007aaa958f1fe19efa1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 419,
        "name": "Frank Zago",
        "email": "fzago@cray.com",
        "username": "fzago.cray"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-20 16:25:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> It would have been nicer to separate the minor PPC-specific fixes\n > (looks like only (unsigned long long) casts) from the major code\n > reorg for clang.  That makes it really hard to see what you\n > actually changed.\n\nI just moved things around and added the casts. I can split if you wish, but that would be 2 dependent patches, which is way more painful to get in than a single patch.",
